Class PropertyPolygon

java.lang.Object
Models.PropertyPolygon
Direct Known Subclasses:
MockedPropertyPolygon
@Layer(BACK_END) public class PropertyPolygon extends Object
The PropertyPolygon class represents a property with a polygonal shape. It includes attributes such as the property ID, owner, geographical location, and shape details.

    • PropertyPolygon

      public PropertyPolygon(int objectId, double parId, String parNum, double shapeLength, double shapeArea, Polygon polygon, String owner, String freguesia, String municipio, String ilha)
      Constructor to initialize a PropertyPolygon object.
      Parameters:
      objectId - Unique identifier for the property.
      parId - Parcel ID associated with the property.
      parNum - Parcel number for the property.
      shapeLength - Length of the shape's boundary.
      shapeArea - Area of the property shape.
      polygon - The polygon representing the shape of the property.
      owner - ID of the owner of the property.
      freguesia - The parish where the property is located.
      municipio - The municipality where the property is located.
      ilha - The island where the property is located.
